Yes. The ecosystem has matured quickly, but it's also fragmented. Most SDKs focus on orchestrating agents rather than defining a standardized agent architecture. That's where I think Bellfre has room to differentiate.

Here's how I'd group the major players:

Framework	Best At	Where Bellfre Differs
LangGraph	Complex workflows, durable execution, state machines	Bellfre would define the agent itself, not just the workflow.
OpenAI Agents SDK	Lightweight OpenAI-native agents, tool use, handoffs	Bellfre should be model-agnostic and focused on architecture.
CrewAI	Role-based multi-agent teams	Bellfre defines standardized agent structure instead of team behavior.
Microsoft Agent Framework / Semantic Kernel	Enterprise and .NET integration	Bellfre could become the portable architecture independent of Microsoft.
Google ADK	Google Cloud-native agents	Bellfre would not be cloud-provider specific.
LlamaIndex	Document-centric agents and RAG	Bellfre treats this as one capability, not the foundation.
What they all have in common

Nearly every framework answers:

"How do I build an AI agent?"

They provide things like:

Prompt management
Memory
Tool calling
Multi-agent orchestration
Workflow execution
Model integration

What they generally don't define is:

A universal agent identity
A portable agent manifest
A lifecycle standard
A discovery representation
A profile model (personal → business → enterprise)

That gap is where Bellfre can live.

I think Bellfre's value proposition is different

Instead of saying:

"We're another agent SDK."

I'd position it as:

"Bellfre is an Agent Architecture SDK."

Meaning:

It defines what a Bellfre-compatible agent looks like.
It provides builders, validators, and runtimes for that architecture.
It can plug into existing orchestration frameworks rather than replace them.

For example:

                Bellfre

          Agent Definition
          Agent Manifest
          Agent Profile
          Agent Discovery
          Tool Contracts
                |
      -------------------------
      |           |           |
   LangGraph   OpenAI SDK   CrewAI

Bellfre becomes the common architectural layer, while the others become execution engines or integrations.

This leads to an important roadmap item

I think we should stop thinking of Bellfre as one SDK.

Instead, the roadmap becomes:

Bellfre SDK

├── Agent SDK
│   ├── Agent Builder
│   ├── Manifest Builder
│   ├── Profile Builder
│   └── Validation
│
├── Tool SDK
│   ├── Tool Builder
