    └── CrewAI Adapter

That positioning is much harder to copy because it isn't trying to beat LangGraph or CrewAI at orchestration. Instead, Bellfre provides the standardized architecture that those frameworks can execute.

One thought I'd suggest adding to the Bellfre vision is:

Bellfre should strive to make an agent portable. If an agent is built with Bellfre, it should be possible to run it locally, in a business environment, or on top of another orchestration framework with minimal changes. That kind of portability is a compelling architectural goal and complements existing interoperability efforts rather than competing with them.

